The paper discusses the design of a library for implementing the actor model in C++11, which is a programming language and software engineering topic (cs.PL, cs.SE). The actor model is a concurrency and distribution model, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing category (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of a thread pool for scheduling actors, which is a data structure and algorithm topic (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance and resource-efficiency of the implementation, which could fall under the machine learning category (cs.LG).
